Permitted Purpose

A Permitted Purpose is any purpose that is both (a) not a Competing Use and
(b) within the Community Tier. Use that is not a Competing Use but that exceeds
the Community Tier is permitted only under a separate commercial license from us
(see the Commercial License section below).

A Competing Use means making the Software available to others in a commercial
product or service that:

1. substitutes for the Software;

2. substitutes for any other product or service we offer using the Software
   that exists as of the date we make the Software available; or

3. offers the same or substantially similar functionality as the Software.

Permitted Purposes specifically include using the Software, within the Community
Tier:

1. for your internal use and access;

2. for non-commercial education;

3. for non-commercial research; and

4. in connection with professional services that you provide to a licensee
   using the Software in accordance with these Terms and Conditions.

Community Tier

Your use is within the Community Tier if any of the following applies:

1. you are an individual using the Software for personal, non-commercial
   purposes;

2. you are using the Software for non-commercial education or non-commercial
   research; or

3. use of the Software is for the benefit of your company, and your company,
   in the prior tax year, has fewer than 50 total individuals working as
   employees and independent contractors, and less than 1,000,000 USD (2019)
   total revenue, and your company has raised no more than 1,000,000 USD (2019)
   in total external or institutional funding (including venture capital,
   private equity, angel, and similar investment) as of the date of your use.

Adjust each 1,000,000 USD threshold for inflation according to the United States
Bureau of Labor Statistics' consumer price index for all urban consumers, U.S.
city average, for all items, not seasonally adjusted, with 1982-1984=100
reference base.

"Your company" is any legal entity, sole proprietorship, or other kind of
organization that you work for, plus all organizations that have control over,
are under the control of, or are under common control with that organization.
"Control" means ownership of substantially all the assets of an entity, or the
power to direct its management and policies by vote, contract, or otherwise.
Control can be direct or indirect.

If your use exceeds the Community Tier, you may obtain a commercial license as
described in the Commercial License section below.

Derivative Models

Except with our prior written permission, you will not use the Software, its
model weights, or any Output to train, fine-tune, distill, adapt, align, or
otherwise create, develop, or improve any machine-learning model or artificial
intelligence system, other than a derivative work of the Software itself that
you license in its entirety under these Terms and Conditions.

This restriction applies whether or not the resulting model or system competes
with the Software, and whether or not the Software is redistributed.

For clarity, this restriction does not by itself prevent you from using Output
for purposes other than developing a machine-learning model or artificial
intelligence system, subject to the rest of these Terms and Conditions. As
between you and us, you own the Output you generate, subject to this Derivative
Models restriction and to these Terms and Conditions.

To request permission, email Vittoria Lanzo at lanzo.vittoria@gmail.com.
Sending a request does not grant you any rights. No permission arises unless and
until we affirmatively approve your request in a written reply from us. Our
silence, non-response, or failure to reply is not permission and must be treated
as a denial. We may grant, condition, or deny any request on a case-by-case
basis in our sole discretion, and any approval is effective only for the use
expressly described in our written reply.

